.TH WEBCAM-TRAY 1 "November 2025" "webcam-tray 1.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
webcam-tray \- System tray icon for controlling VirtualCam service
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B webcam-tray
[\fICOMMAND\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B webcam-tray
provides a system tray icon for easy control of the VirtualCam systemd service.
It supports Intel IPU6 cameras and standard USB webcams, creating a virtual camera
device using v4l2loopback and GStreamer.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B tray
Start the system tray icon (default)
.TP
.B start
Start the VirtualCam service
.TP
.B stop
Stop the VirtualCam service
.TP
.B toggle
Toggle the VirtualCam service state
.TP
.B status
Show the current service status
.TP
.B logs
Open the service logs in a viewer
.TP
.B config
Open the configuration file
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display help message
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/webcam-tray/config
User configuration file
.TP
.I ~/.config/systemd/user/virtualcam.service
systemd user service file
.TP
.I $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/webcam-tray-pipe
Named pipe for tray communication
.TP
.I $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/webcam-tray.pid
PID file for instance tracking
.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file supports the following options:
.TP
.B UPDATE_INTERVAL
Interval in seconds for status updates (default: 2)
.TP
.B SERVICE_NAME
Name of the systemd service to control (default: virtualcam.service)
.TP
.B ICON
Icon name from the system icon theme (default: camera-web)
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.TP
.B Required
yad, zenity, libnotify, systemd, gstreamer, v4l2-utils
.TP
.B Optional
v4l2loopback-dkms, ipu6-camera-hal (for Intel IPU6), gst-plugin-icamerasrc
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Start the tray icon:
.B webcam-tray
.TP
Start the service from command line:
.B webcam-tray start
.TP
View logs:
.B webcam-tray logs
.TP
Open configuration:
.B webcam-tray config
.SH SETUP
First-time setup requires running:
.TP
.B webcam-tray-setup
or
.B ./setup-service.sh
.PP
This will detect your camera hardware and generate the appropriate systemd service file.
.SH LOGGING
All operations are logged using systemd's journal. View logs with:
.TP
.B journalctl --user -u virtualcam.service
.TP
.B journalctl -t webcam-tray
.SH AUTOSTART
To enable autostart on login, create a desktop entry in:
.TP
.I ~/.config/autostart/webcam-tray.desktop
.PP
Or use the GUI configuration tool:
.B webcam-tray-config
